Nottingham Forest centre-back Yohann Benalouane is a target for Turkish giants Fenerbahce, according to Turkish football website Fanatik . Fenerbahce, who finished sixth in the Super Lig last term, have already concluded one deal for a Championship defender this summer, securing a deal for Huddersfield Town centre-back Mathias Jorgensen. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network But it is now being reported that Fenerbahce could further strengthen their centre-back options with a move for Tunisia international Benalouane.